        "whyGood": "50K miles on a C4 Corvette convertible is almost unbelievably low \u2014 these tend to be well-cared-for cars. The LT1 V8 is a strong, serviceable engine. At $8,450 with verified no-accidents history, this is exceptional value for an American icon. Private seller adds authenticity.",
        "whatToVerify": "C4 rubber degrades with age \u2014 check all weatherstripping, top seals, and the rear-window plastic (often yellowed/cracked). Test AC (C4s lose refrigerant). Check for rear differential whine. Inspect convertible top frame for binding or broken struts. Verify the top operates smoothly and seals completely at speed.",
